cent — warm, warm! — up to my room number on my hotel floor in a remote country, up, up, in one of those express elevators manned by the delicate hands — my own in a negative picture — of dark-skinned men with sinking stomachs and rising hearts, never attaining Paradise, which is not a roof garden; and from the depths of the stag-headed hall old President Azureus came at a quick pace, his arms open, his faded blue eyes beaming in advance, his long wrinkled upper lip quivering —

